Title   : Broker’s call: Schloss Bangalore
Source  : www.thehindubusinessline.com
Published: 2025-09-23T14:01:08
Fetched : 2025-09-23T17:10:50.581254
URL     : https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/markets/brokers-call-schloss-bangalore/article70084217.ece
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Target: ₹605
CMP: ₹438.50
Schloss Bangalore Ltd (Leela) owns and operates luxury hotels under the ‘The Leela’ brand, which is widely recognised for superior architecture and luxury experience – enabling the company to deliver superior average room rate (ARR )in the segment. The demand-supply outlook for the luxury hospitality segment in India continues to be favourable, with total demand for luxury rooms estimated to grow at a CAGR of 10.6 per cent over FY24-FY28E against supply growth of only 5.9 per cent over the same period.
Leela’s brand recognition, built over almost 40 years, highlights the company’s ability to deliver luxury experiences that are difficult to replicate.
Leela has laid out an aggressive expansion plan, which will see its room inventory increase from 1,224 owned keys to 1,978 owned keys by FY30E.
We expect the company to report 17/18 per cent CAGR in Revenue/EBITDA over FY25-28E, aided by 10 per cent CAGR in ARR and gradual improvement in occupancy. It can generate a cumulative FCFE of about ₹1,800 crore during FY26E-FY30E, which enables it to comfortably fund the BKC expansion (Leela’s share ₹2,000 crore).
We initiate coverage with a Buy rating and a target price of ₹605, valuing the company at 22x Jun’27 EBITDA (24 per cent discount to Indian Hotel’s target multiple).
Published on September 23, 2025

