Financial metrics temporarily unavailable (rate limited) - 2025-09-23

Title   : Atlanta Electricals IPO: Issue subscribed 2 times so far on Day 2; GMP at 12%. What analysts say? 
Source  : economictimes.indiatimes.com
Published: 2025-09-23T08:50:32
Fetched : 2025-09-23T17:20:55.735507
URL     : https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/ipos/fpos/atlanta-electricals-ipo-issue-subscribed-2-times-so-far-on-day-2-gmp-at-12-what-analysts-say/articleshow/124066410.cms
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Non-institutional investors drove enthusiasm, subscribing to the issue by 2.66 times, followed by the retail investors, who subscribed to the issue by 1.8 times. Meanwhile, the qualified institutional buyers (QIBs) applied for 26,25,762 shares of the company against the 18,05,134 shares reserved for them, making a subscription of 1.45 times.
The issue opened for subscription on September 22 and will close on September 24. The public issue is valued at Rs 687 crore and includes a fresh issue of Rs 400 crore along with an offer-for-sale (OFS) component of Rs 287 crore.
The price band was fixed between Rs 718 and Rs 754 per share, with a minimum application size of 19 equity shares.
The net proceeds from the fresh issue are earmarked for repayment of existing borrowings, funding working capital requirements, and other general corporate purposes. Following the issue, promoter shareholding is expected to reduce from 94% to 83%.
About Atlanta Electricals
With a legacy spanning over 30 years, Atlanta Electricals is one of India’s major transformer manufacturers. The company has scaled its production capabilities to manufacture transformers with capacities up to 500 MVA and 765 kV. It caters to both public and private sector clients, with public sector undertakings contributing over 80% of its total order book. As of March 31, 2025, the company's order book stood at Rs 16,430 million.Atlanta Electricals financial performance
In FY25, Atlanta Electricals delivered strong growth, with revenue rising 43% year-on-year to Rs 12,442 million. Profit after tax surged to Rs 1,186 million from Rs 634 million in FY24. The EBITDA margin improved to 16%, and the return on equity was a robust 33.9%.At the upper end of the price band, the Atlanta Electricals IPO is priced at a P/E multiple of 48.8x FY25 earnings and an EV/EBITDA of 30.1x.
The macro environment for transformers is promising, driven by rising electricity demand, renewable energy integration, EV charging infrastructure, and high-speed rail projects. Atlanta Electricals holds approvals from major institutions such as the Power Grid Corporation of India and the Ministry of Railways, enhancing its future revenue visibility.
What analysts say about Atlanta Electricals IPO?
Anand Rathi Research has given the Atlanta Electricals IPO a “Subscribe – Long Term” recommendation. Despite noting the valuation as fully priced, the brokerage highlighted the company’s robust order book, diversified product offerings, and strong positioning in a growth-oriented sector.Further, Geojit Investments recommends a ‘Subscribe’ rating with a long-term investment perspective for the issue.
“At the upper price band of Rs 754, AEL is available at a P/E ratio of 49x (FY25 diluted basis) and appears premium compared to its peers. AEL’s strong fundamentals, healthy return ratios, capacity expansion, robust order book, and strategic initiatives support its valuation, making it appealing for long-term investors in India’s power infrastructure growth,” the brokerage firm said in its note.
(Disclaimer: Recommendations, suggestions, views and opinions given by the experts are their own. These do not represent the views of The Economic Times)
