Financial metrics temporarily unavailable (rate limited) - 2025-09-23

Title   : MRF says Chennai plant strike illegal; operations partly continue
Source  : www.thehindubusinessline.com
Published: 2025-09-23T09:42:23
Fetched : 2025-09-23T17:50:45.946874
URL     : https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/companies/mrf-terms-strike-by-some-employees-at-tiruvottiyur-plant-as-illegal/article70083721.ece
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
MRF Ltd has said that some of the workmen at the company’s manufacturing plant at Tiruvottiyur in North Chennai have gone on a strike about payment of annual insurance premium as advance, and opposing the hiring of trainees under the National Apprentice Promotion Scheme (NAPS), Prime Minister’s Internship Scheme (PMIS) and Naan Mudhalvan Scheme.
In an announcement to the Bombay Stock Exchange, the company said, “Tiruvottiyur factory is one of the ten factories the company has across India. It may be noted that the strike is illegal. The operations of the factory are being partly continued with the help of the workmen who are not part of the strike. The company is taking necessary steps to restore normalcy at the earliest.”
CITU says 800 workers on strike, production hit
businessline had reported on Saturday, quoting A Soundararajan, State President, CITU, that nearly 800 workers at MRF’s Wimco Nagar manufacturing unit are on strike over the annual medical insurance premium. “Production has been affected in the last one week,” he then said.
At the close, the company’s share price ended at ₹1,55,340, up by ₹2,490 (+1.63 per cent).
Published on September 23, 2025

