Title   : Seshaasai Technologies IPO subscribed 35% on Day 1 so far. Check GMP, price band, other details 
Source  : economictimes.indiatimes.com
Published: 2025-09-23T08:19:21
Fetched : 2025-09-23T18:09:08.749129
URL     : https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/ipos/fpos/seshaasai-technologies-ipo-subscribed-35-on-day-1-so-far-check-gmp-price-band-other-details/articleshow/124065790.cms
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
By 12:15 PM, the retail portion had been bid 46%, while non-institutional investors (NIIs) bid for 54% of shares allotted to them. Qualified institutional buyers (QIBs) had yet to participate.
Seshaasai Technologies GMP
The Seshaasai Technologies IPO is priced in the band of Rs 402–423 per share. The last traded grey market premium (GMP) was Rs 85 as of 11:35 AM on Tuesday, implying an estimated listing price of Rs 508 per share and a potential gain of around 20% from the upper band.Investors can bid for a minimum lot of 35 shares, translating to an application amount of Rs 14,805 at the top end of the price range.
The Seshaasai Technologies IPO comprises a fresh issue of Rs 480 crore and an offer-for-sale (OFS) of Rs 333 crore. At the upper end of the band, the post-issue market capitalisation of Seshaasai Technologies is expected to reach Rs 6,844 crore.
Use of proceeds
Proceeds from the fresh issue of the offer will be used to expand metal card manufacturing capacity at Navi Mumbai and Bengaluru facilities, prepay Rs 300 crore of borrowings, and fund general corporate purposes.Business profile and market position
Seshaasai Technologies is one of India’s top two payment card manufacturers, commanding a 31.9% market share in FY25, up from 25% in FY23. The company serves more than 700 clients, including HDFC Bank, ICICI Bank, SBI, HDFC Life, and PhonePe, with the BFSI sector contributing roughly 84% of FY25 revenues. Its product portfolio spans debit and credit cards, biometric and metal cards, dynamic CVV cards, and payment-on-the-go devices.The company has diversified into RFID and IoT solutions across retail, logistics, automotive, and healthcare, operating 24 manufacturing units across seven locations and two dedicated R&D labs.
Financial performance and valuation
Seshaasai Technologies has reported robust financial growth over the past three years. Revenue increased from Rs 1,146 crore in FY23 to Rs 1,463 crore in FY25, a CAGR of 13%, while PAT jumped from Rs 108 crore to Rs 222 crore, representing a CAGR of 43%. EBITDA margins expanded to 24.6% in FY25 from 17.4% in FY23, with ROE at 34.8% and ROCE at 31.9%. The company’s debt-to-equity ratio improved to 0.55.Valuation and outlook
At the upper price band, the IPO is valued at a P/E of 28x FY25 earnings and a P/BV of 6.1x. Analysts highlight the company’s leadership position, high client stickiness, and growth potential in the payments and IoT ecosystem.Also read: Technology sector based mutual funds lose 4% in 1 year. Will Trump’s H1-B visa policy add more pressure?
SMIFS has issued a "Subscribe" recommendation, citing Seshaasai’s market leadership, diversified technology-driven offerings, strong financials, and expansion into international markets.
The IPO will remain open for subscription until September 25.
