Title   : JCB India inaugurates its new dealership, KUN Capital Automotive in Tiruchirappalli
Source  : www.thehindubusinessline.com
Published: 2025-09-23T13:40:23
Fetched : 2025-09-23T18:09:37.166742
URL     : https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/companies/jcb-india-inaugurates-its-new-dealership-kun-capital-automotive-in-tiruchirappalli/article70084887.ece
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
JCB India, a leading manufacturer of earthmoving and construction equipment, inaugurated its dealership KUN Capital Automotive in Tiruchirapalli, Tamil Nadu.
With 86 trained sales and service professionals on site, the facility is equipped with six workshop bays, one welding bay, and a Pre-Dispatch Inspection Bay.
Other highlights include a fully operational LiveLink Command Centre for real-time machine monitoring, a Workshop-on-Wheels van, and a dedicated Parts and Service van — ensuring customers receive timely and seamless support, says a release.
Deepak Shetty, CEO and Managing Director - JCB India, said, “Tamil Nadu is India’s second-largest economy and contributes over 8 per cent to the national GDP. It’s a leader in industrialization, with strong manufacturing clusters across automobiles, textiles, and electronics. Also exciting is the state’s forward-looking infrastructure push. In Tiruchirapalli, developments such as the Cauvery Riverfront Project, Trichy International Airport expansion, new ring roads, smart city initiatives under AMRUT, and water body rejuvenation projects are accelerating the demand for reliable earthmoving equipment.”
In addition to this new dealership in Trichy, KUN Capital Automotive has its footprint across Tamil Nadu with seven other strategically located branches in Thanjavur, Karur, Pudukkottai, Ariyalur, Perambalur, Palani, and Dindigul, enhancing accessibility for customers in the region, the release said.
Published on September 23, 2025

Title   : Commodity Radar: China’s restocking, weak dollar slow copper’s September march. Time to buy on dips for short term gains? 
Source  : economictimes.indiatimes.com
Published: 2025-09-23T09:09:59
Fetched : 2025-09-23T18:09:37.166742
URL     : https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/commodities/commodity-radar-chinas-restocking-weak-dollar-slow-coppers-september-march-time-to-buy-on-dips-for-short-term-gains/articleshow/124066749.cms
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The September copper contracts on the MCX were trading around Rs 910.75 per kg, up by Rs 0.50 or 0.05% over the Monday closing price. The 3-month contracts on the LME were trading around $9,972.50 per metric ton while those on SHFE were marginally down at 0.1%.
Ajit Mishra, Senior Vice President, Research at Religare Broking, said that copper prices have seen a notable upward movement in September 2025, driven by supply disruptions at major mines in Chile, Peru, and Indonesia, tightening global chains and fueling bullish sentiment among investors. In his view, the demand remains robust due to ongoing infrastructure projects, the global energy transition, and higher requirements from tech sectors such as data centers and artificial intelligence.
“Despite strong demand, refined copper imports in China fell below expectations last month, adding further volatility to the market. Speculative activity remains high, and the International Energy Agency continues to emphasize copper’s role as a critical mineral for the next super cycle,” Mishra said.
Tech view
Technically, the MCX daily chart shows copper recently tested Rs 921.50 on the upside, before experiencing profit booking and pulling back towards the 900 zone. The price has maintained above key moving averages (50, 100, and 200 DMA), signaling underlying strength but encountering resistance and forming a potential bearish reversal pattern.
Weekly RSI hovers near 60, indicating some overbought conditions, and MACD shows early signs of negative crossover, hinting at consolidation or minor correction ahead.
The Religare Broking analyst expects copper to remain in a moderately bullish-to-sideways range over this week and places support near Rs 890–895 and resistance at Rs 925–930.
Copper daily chart
Copper trading strategy
Mishra said that short-term corrections could offer a buy on dips opportunity, but traders should be cautious if prices break below the 890 zone, which may trigger deeper profit-booking.
