Title   : Gainers & Losers: Refex Industries, Adani Total Gas among 6 top movers on Tuesday. Here’s why 
Source  : economictimes.indiatimes.com
Published: 2025-09-23T11:16:33
Fetched : 2025-09-23T18:10:05.907940
URL     : https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/stocks/news/gainers-losers-refex-industries-adani-total-gas-among-6-top-movers-on-tuesday-heres-why/slideshow/124069595.cms
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Sep 23, 2025
Indian benchmark indices ended with declines for the third day in a row amid some volatility. FMCG and IT stocks were the main reasons for today’s lacklustre show. The Nifty ended at 25,169, declining by 32 points or 0.13%, while the BSE Sensex closed at 82,102, falling 57 points or 0.07%. Here are six stocks that saw action today:
Image Source: iStock
Shares of Refex Industries ended 16% up in Tuesday’s trade after the company announced that its board approved a composite scheme of amalgamation and arrangement to unlock the potential of its Green Mobility business. The stock settled at Rs 391.90.
Image Source: iStock
Shares of Gujarat Mineral Development Corporation (GMDC) today hit a fresh lifetime high of Rs 642 before closing at Rs 625.60, up 60.45 or 10.70%. The multibagger PSU mining stock has been in top form 128% in the past six months supported by robust investor interest, sectoral tailwinds, and optimism around the company’s rare earth mining initiatives.
Image Source: iStock
Shares of Tata Investment Corporation closed with over 10% gains at Rs 8,036 on the NSE reacting to the company's announcement of record date for the purpose of 1:10 stock split. It has fixed the record date on October 14.
Image Source: iStock
Shares of Vodafone Idea today ended with 4.3% gains at Rs 8.75 on the NSE amid hopes of some relief from India's Supreme Court on the government's Adjusted Gross Revenue (AGR) dues demand of Rs 9,450 crore. The apex court will hear the case on Friday, September 26.
Image Source: iStock
Shares of Adani Total Gas (ATG) today fell 7.7% to close at Rs 780.75 amid profit booking in the counter following a two-sessions rally where the stocks gained 29%. The gains were on the back of a Sebi clean chit to Adani Group companies on alleged fund diversion and violation of related party transaction norms.
Image Source: iStock
Shares of LT Foods closed 4.7% lower at Rs 435.05 on the NSE today amid significant selling pressure in FMCG stocks. It was its second successive negative closing.
Image Source: iStock
