Financial metrics temporarily unavailable (rate limited) - 2025-09-23

Title   : Infinity Infoway to raise ₹25 cr via IPO on BSE SME
Source  : www.thehindubusinessline.com
Published: 2025-09-23T11:01:50
Fetched : 2025-09-23T18:16:10.417034
URL     : https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/markets/infinity-infoway-to-raise-25-cr-via-ipo-on-bse-sme/article70084248.ece
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Infinity Infoway, a SaaS provider company specializing in delivering customized and integrated Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) solutions, plans to raise ₹25 crore through initial public offering on the BSE SME platform.
The company will issue about 15.75 lakh equity shares in the price band of ₹147 - ₹155 a share.
The IPO opens for subscription on Tuesday.
The net proceeds from the IPO will be used for developing proprietary technology solution “ZEROTOUCH”, purchase of new IT infrastructure and certification, funding of tender deposits and earnest money deposits towards tenders, funding the incremental working capital requirements and general corporate purposes.
Holani Consultants will be the lead manager while Bigshare Services has been appointed as registrar.
Bhaveshkumar Dhirajlal Gadhethriya, promoter and Managing Directot, Infinity Infoway said with over 17 years of experience in the IT sector, the company’s SaaS solutions have empowered education, industries and government organisations.
The company has a strong presence across 38 universities and 11 industries and continues to drive efficiency through flagship Campus Management System and Infinity ERP, he said.
Ashok Holani, Director of Holani Consultants said the SaaS and EdTech sectors are witnessing rapid growth, driven by digital transformation, automation and progressive reforms such as the National Education Policy.
The IPO will empower the company to accelerate innovation, strengthen its IT infrastructure and expand operations to serve a larger customer base across education, industry and government organizations, he said.
Published on September 23, 2025

