Title   : Nifty holds 25,000, rally seen towards 25,500; Motherson Sumi, Aadhar Housing Finance among top picks 
Source  : economictimes.indiatimes.com
Published: 2025-09-23T10:51:22
Fetched : 2025-09-23T18:19:07.730235
URL     : https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/stocks/news/nifty-holds-25000-rally-seen-towards-25500-motherson-sumi-aadhar-housing-finance-among-top-picks/articleshow/124069084.cms
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Commenting on the current market setup, market expert Vinay Rajani in an interview to ET Now said, “So yes, we are passing through the correction phase and running correction we must say, because the 1000-point recovery from the lower level on 29th August we saw Nifty making a low at 24,400 and after that we have seen that recent swing high was at 25,448. So more than 1000-point rally backed by the strong global cues. And now for last three trading sessions we have been witnessing some profit booking in the overall trend. So, this seems more like a profit booking and correction phase in an overall bullish trend.”
Rajani further explained that technical support levels remain intact. “If I were to see the entire this 1000-point rally and if I have to take the Fibonacci retracement of that, the 38.2% retracement of the entire rally comes around 25,050 odd level, 20 days exponential moving average is also placed around 25,040 odd level. So, there was a strong support around that level. Today's low is 25,084. So, it looks like that the way some sectors are participating in this market like auto, metal, and some PSU banks are also showing strength, so it seems that overall trend remaining bullish.”
Bank Nifty has been showing leadership, supported by stocks such as Axis Bank and NBFCs like Bajaj Finserv. Rajani added, “Though we have been correcting for last three session in the Nifty but overall mood is and sentiment is bullish, so dip should be bought into 25,050, 25,000 is a very strong support. So, dip should be bought into. It might happen that it will not break today's low itself from here on. So, today's low becomes a strong support for the Nifty and I am expecting resumption of an uptrend.”
On the upside, Rajani is optimistic about crossing key levels. “On the upside, yes, there is a good chance that the Nifty will break 25,500, the recent swing higher was 25,448. I am expecting Nifty to cross that level in the coming time and whatever trading long position traders have, should have a stop loss of 24,900 and yes, bias is on the positive side and I am expecting Nifty to cross 25,500.”
When asked about trading opportunities in the current market, Rajani pointed towards select midcap plays. “So, as you said autos, yes, they have been doing well and still they are holding their uptrend, but most of the largecap auto stocks have already performed. They look bit stretched as of now. There is an opportunity in the auto ancillary space where we can see some fresh breakouts coming in, so auto ancillary space still we believe should do well. So, one of the stocks from the space is the Motherson Sumi which we like as a trading bet. So, Motherson Sumi can be bought around 111.70, trading stop loss I would suggest around 108, on the upside we are expecting a target of 116.”
He also highlighted an NBFC pick. “The second pick I would take from the NBFC space, housing finance space that is, Aadhar Housing Finance that is looking attractive on the chart. So, after some running correction, the stock has resumed the uptrend from today's low. So around 535, one can go long. I would suggest a stop loss at 522. On the upside, you can expect a short-term target around 565.”
With strong technical support levels, sectoral participation, and stock-specific opportunities, market experts remain confident that the Nifty will resume its uptrend and march past the 25,500 mark in the near term.
